Author: jaxxxxxxyyyy
Content:
@everyone 

a reminder to everyone late at night (apology to all of you with the ping): do not be easily fooled by the narratives that had been circulated. Always try to confirm them by looking at different outlets and news to see their truths. There had been multiple rumors spread out about the targeting of Chindos, which I myself as a Chindo found it to be suspicious. 

For those who had heard the news about Tangcity, BSD and Alsut being raided with violent protests, I speak to these rumors as someone who lives near there. I had been out from 3 PM to 10 PM from Tangcity to BSD: none of them were true except the fact that Tangcity only have a few areas having protests (which you can take the back road such as Jalan Tol Banjar to avoid them). Alsut doesn't even has any news about protest to begin with, and riots in ICE BSD had been debunked to be not true at all.

Do not be scared or baited by these narratives. Always try to check other news outlets multiple times to confirm rumors about it, then have your mapping apps to mapped out areas that had been confirmed with the ongoing demonstrations. Don't let the rumors scares you off, but be brave enough to question any abnormalities and suspicions behind it. Let us keep the support for our demonstrators even when we are not on the streets with them. Stay safe and keep yourself informed about your own surroundings. 

Never let your status as a minority scared you, but strengthen you to be better and aware than the others.
